  "text": "Consider N base stations (BS) intercepting the narrowband signals transmitted by L possible sources. Each BS which knows its coordinates is equipped with an antenna array consisting of M elements. Denote the lth unknown target position by the vector of coordinates l P . We use the far-field point-target model, which is commonly used for source localization due to its simplicity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Based on this model, the received signal observed by the nth BS is given by",
